sub_title: Biology Teacher at Eerste Christelijk Lyceum
summary:
Master student of neuroscience with a specific interest in the neurobiology of sensory systems in different animal species, from the subcellular to the ecological level. I am working towards obtaining a teaching degree in high school biology, where I aim to combine my specific neuroscientific interests, my broad biological interests, and my interest in education.
I am also politically active, focusing on environmentalism, animal welfare, and human rights, and exploring the intersections between these topics on a systemic level.
Music has also been a long standing interest, seeping through many aspects of my life.
